00:18:31,583 --> 00:18:33,333
doin' any cuttin'
around here is me!

484
00:18:34,625 --> 00:18:36,416
[AKENO] Bring it on, baby,
and while you're at it,

485
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:38,750
hug me and squeeze me
and hug me and squeeze me!

486
00:18:39,166 --> 00:18:40,708
[CAPTAIN SWORDSMAN] Enough!

487
00:18:41,666 --> 00:18:42,875
[AKENO] Of what?

488
00:18:42,958 --> 00:18:44,708
[SUN] Who are you?

489
00:18:47,583 --> 00:18:48,791
This is insane.

490
00:18:48,875 --> 00:18:51,500
I expected some
challenges, but THIS...

491
00:18:53,083 --> 00:18:55,333
[CAPTAIN SWORDSMAN] This
is a total freaking nightmare!

492
00:18:57,375 --> 00:18:58,833
[CAPTAIN SWORDSMAN]
The Fish Shot brings out

493
00:18:58,916 --> 00:19:00,333
the hidden desires in people.

494
00:19:00,416 --> 00:19:01,541
So what you're telling me is

495
00:19:01,625 --> 00:19:04,458
that even after
drinking it, Sun Seto...

496
00:19:04,541 --> 00:19:05,875
[AKENO] Yes...

497
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:07,666
She's still protecting
Nagasumi above everything else.

498
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:10,708
So all you did was
discover her true desire.

499
00:19:10,791 --> 00:19:13,333
Well, we're back
to square one it seems.

500
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:15,916
Breaking them up might
be impossible, Captain.

501
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,583
If you ask me.

502
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,583
[CAPTAIN SWORDSMAN]
Training swordsman Akeno...

503
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:23,083
...you're to continue
monitoring those

504
00:19:23,166 --> 00:19:25,166
two as a Mermaid
Exam administrator.

505
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:26,541
Understood?

506
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:29,666
[AKENO] Yes...
I understand, Captain.

507
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,375
You have to atone
for this blunder

508
00:19:31,458 --> 00:19:32,708
and the only
way to do that is by

509
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:34,708
carrying your mission
through to the end.

510
00:19:34,791 --> 00:19:36,625
So do it right this time.

511
00:19:39,708 --> 00:19:41,083
[AKENO] Yes, sir.

512
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:47,666
[SUN] Nagasumi,
over here! Hurry!

513
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,791
[NAGASUMI] Sun, wait!
What's going on?

514
00:19:50,208 --> 00:19:52,666
[SUN] Just follow me,
quick! Come on!

515
00:19:54,125 --> 00:19:55,291
See there?

516
00:19:55,916 --> 00:19:59,250
[NAGASUMI] Wow.
A full moon.

517
00:20:00,541 --> 00:20:01,833
Pretty, isn't it?

518
00:20:01,916 --> 00:20:03,708
The minute I saw it I
knew I wanted to share

519
00:20:03,791 --> 00:20:05,750
it with ya alone
and with nobody else.

520
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:08,166
But do ya wanna know why?

521
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:09,750
Cause on this trip,
we haven't had a chance

522
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:11,666
to have a special
moment together.

523
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:18,125
Oh, Sun...
You're the best.

524
00:20:26,666 --> 00:20:27,666
[NAGASUMI] These
last couple of days

525
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:29,041
have been pretty rough on me.

526
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:30,333
But you know what?

527
00:20:30,416 --> 00:20:33,125
Seeing this with you
now makes it all worth it.

528
00:20:35,125 --> 00:20:40,125
♪

529
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,500
[VOICES] Masa Today!

530
00:22:14,625 --> 00:22:16,875
Been awhile, hasn't it...?

531
00:22:16,958 --> 00:22:19,708
You haven't come
to visit in quite some time.

532
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:23,500
[MASA] Oh, you know.
This and that...

533
00:22:23,583 --> 00:22:25,416
Were you worried about me?

534
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:26,916
Not really.

535
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,250
[door opens and closes
with chimes ringing]

536
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:31,166
[PROPRIETRESS]
Hello and welcome.

537
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:34,625
[MASA] I've gotta admit, I'm
impressed you found this place.

538
00:22:34,708 --> 00:22:37,083
I never expected
to see you here.

539
00:22:37,166 --> 00:22:39,583
[MASA] I suppose you
just got off work, huh?

540
00:22:39,666 --> 00:22:42,833
Well, in that case, let's do
some nice, relaxing drinking.

541
00:22:42,916 --> 00:22:45,750
[MASA] Owner... Let's have one
of the usual if you don't mind.

542
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,125
Sure...

543
00:22:47,666 --> 00:22:48,750
[MASA] You'll like that.

544
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:51,791
It's "The Sad Father,"
a house specialty.

545
00:22:51,875 --> 00:22:53,041
It's slightly bitter,

546
00:22:53,125 --> 00:22:55,458
but I think you'll find
it takes the edge off.

547
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:57,750
[MASA] I can tell you're upset,

548
00:22:57,833 --> 00:22:59,708
but this is all a big
misunderstanding.

549
00:22:59,791 --> 00:23:00,958
You're wife and I--

550
00:23:01,041 --> 00:23:02,541
Just give her back.

551
00:23:03,375 --> 00:23:05,166
I've told you, there's
nothing going on man.

552
00:23:05,250 --> 00:23:07,291
Don't lie to me!
I've seen how she looks at you!

553
00:23:07,375 --> 00:23:09,583
It's only a matter of time
before she leaves me!

554
00:23:09,666 --> 00:23:11,416
You're just imagining
things, pal.

555
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:13,750
You're the only one
who understands me, kitty.

556
00:23:13,833 --> 00:23:15,416
You'll never leave me, right?

557
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:20,541
[MASA] Let's get really
sauced tonight, okay?

558
00:23:20,625 --> 00:23:21,750
Don't worry...

559
00:23:21,833 --> 00:23:24,708
I'll stay by your side
until you pass out.

560
00:23:24,791 --> 00:23:27,083
[DAD] You will?
You're a great guy.

561
00:23:27,166 --> 00:23:28,958
[MASA] None of
the either please!

562
00:23:29,041 --> 00:23:30,458
[DAD] But give me back my wife!

563
00:23:30,541 --> 00:23:32,916
[MASA] Whoa, whoa! And
none of that either, please.

